headline: Booz Allen, Accenture stocks fall on Pentagon contract cancellations
summary: Investing.com -- Shares of Booz Allen Hamilton Holding (NYSE:BAH) dropped 2.3%, while Accenture plc (NYSE:ACN) saw a 2.2% decrease following the Pentagon’s decision to terminate $5 billion in IT services and consulting contracts. This move comes amid efforts to reduce consultancy spending deemed non-essential by Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth, stating the work could be more efficiently carried out by Pentagon staff.
